      "source_refs": [
        {
          "path": "literature/2510.23470/arxiv_source/aa57036-25corr_clean.tex",
          "start_line": 190,
          "end_line": 190,
          "context": "Observations were made during the 2019B Semester when the VLA was in D-configuration, choosing the C band  (4-8\\,GHz) and X band (8-12\\,GHz).\n\nThe biggest limitation was to choose candidates that have declination  $>-\\ang{16}$ in order to minimise shadowing from the antennas\\footnote{\\url{https://science.nrao.edu/facilities/vla/docs/manuals/obsguide/dynsched/antenna-shadowing}} for sources that are low in the sky.\nSince the D-configuration is the tightest layout for the VLA, there is a high chance the targets with declination $\\le-\\ang{16}$ will be overshadowed.\nThis limitation excluded almost half of the candidates."
        }
      ],
      "evidence": "Observations were made during the 2019B Semester when the VLA was in D-configuration, choosing the C band  (4-8\\,GHz) and X band (8-12\\,GHz).\n\nThe biggest limitation was to choose candidates that have declination  $>-\\ang{16}$ in order to minimise shadowing from the antennas\\footnote{\\url{https://science.nrao.edu/facilities/vla/docs/manuals/obsguide/dynsched/antenna-shadowing}} for sources that are low in the sky.\nSince the D-configuration is the tightest layout for the VLA, there is a high chance the targets with declination $\\le-\\ang{16}$ will be overshadowed.\nThis limitation excluded almost half of the candidates.",
      "comments": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "resource-002",
      "kind": "external_url",
      "url": "https://science.nrao.edu/facilities/vla/docs/manuals/oss2019B/performance/resolution",
