      "evidence": "For D-configuration, the observing limits (i.e,~observable angular scales of the target\\footnote{\\url{https://science.nrao.edu/facilities/vla/docs/manuals/oss2019B/performance/resolution}}) are between \\ang{;;12} and \\ang{;;240} for C band, and between \\ang{;;7.2} and \\ang{;;145} for the X band.\nIf the target is outside those limits, the array will not be able to resolve the image or will lose flux on large scales.\nTo decide which of the remaining objects we would include in the observation, we measured the size of the bow shocks from the available IR maps online.\\footnote{\\url{https://aladin.u-strasbg.fr}}\n\nFrom those that had the appropriate size, we chose a sample of the brightest ones, and added three extra targets of special interest, namely the bow shocks of \\bdforty, \\bdsixty and \\zoph.",
